document_title: Is false labor dangerous? Causes, signs, prevention
subsection_content:
False labor is labor that has symptoms that are quite similar to real labor, but they are not the usual signs of impending birth. Pregnant women can experience these types of contractions at any time during pregnancy. Sometimes, this is considered a "stepping stone" that shows that real labor is about to happen. Sometimes, you feel contractions in the lower abdomen at the end of the second trimester, or even earlier, but do not cause cervical dilation, and that is definitely false labor.
False labor has symptoms quite similar to real labor
Many pregnant mothers confuse these two labors. If you have never experienced childbirth, pay attention to the typical signs of this phenomenon so you don't worry too much. (first)
